[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test adjustments**\n\nI'm thinking about improving the test catch. Maybe I shouldn't include an assertion for NativeImageSupport? But then again, skipping feels off based on existing catches in the test. The developer mentioned not skipping Native Image execution with early returns, which adds some complexity. For unsupported dynamic class loading, I know that an exception pattern is allowed. It's a bit challenging to balance all these requirements!\n\n**Resolving Java imports**\n\nI’m thinking about whether Java imports can be consistent. It seems like having \"Java\" after \"org\" in JavaEight violates the rule of \"Java imports first.\" I should probably look into whether checkstyle accepted this. Maybe I’ll try to imitate Java first followed by org, just to keep things tidy. Also, it seems like I need to create a file to make these adjustments properly. Let's work this out!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_087035331d79e921016a21e1891b108195b5412cd9a17d81a1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqIeGeGgZve4jcv4sKc5asnwN3hd8rfnaC25Z2n_90hQZ67tSUwXOn1Ou7gMcXLfeRtocjHCqaAM8ckCHo8X4i5Z7sYmYu9DJiX1djsFGddAszOymeEKY8epr7SC7CGc_CNlS3ave4hMDrtgnmG_QIPHfQ2yX8c8PmQ0Xk5eBprxAnl5-hQhm1OcIsxjVWJFPC4CwNaZMk-qZ-9SJ8mLCUK43uMWcWXcxYvcM4P1ib87EXDpV9_nS0XVqtwAnZaiiJBcgD4aS3pM40E3EFdVVt-KI-HaX6JJmVDfQyEgqCO-0P3iQgMS85Is9v-eG_PCcttNW_b65cXa_0PaToMsjdlb_qk2p5ALpK2EA3zJMNLDYQULbHJX4OZ9ciSnnaLNdEnR6953H81nwasB8srMsKANu79RoK5DG7MuNHtWWYkhldi11kxB03iJ0AWSbjt6b18975xoykcZgSdAtIEn6SSPCqLypPKEoTJsTedjzMI3g6jTQ67l_m1N_J2W8sZil19KknpF1TbdN5Qh3DnSOg35usf_V9znboOcdhRisQ-fAEpJSord2GvpysMbmj8aODHLWQsc9pcgLMopGQEp-KWw9wwR_TpZutQt3yjtQHoRX8l5HAJ3-KVA9rGZOe3Wr6UN7Eoh13Y7wEQ4GkJ9shAXDpLV_5F91M4_NB4WEkOWZg_KHTJGAJGkY7NIrSxny77dsadrbbdzjiaFedktaTxhwqfo45MQCnFtuBU-fpfqHFX8HZ_TzvM5j7kOEoE5yO2ChrDp9wPnfhr3oprU2NoGhp_CeVwGMojn8qLru60-bpJVKzt6G1Af17BLYB